tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE client_health_records (
  client_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  client_name VARCHAR(50),
  date_of_birth DATE,
  address VARCHAR(100),
  email VARCHAR(50),
  phone_number VARCHAR(15)
)

CREATE TABLE TreatmentPlans (
    plan_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    client_id INT,
    treatment_description VARCHAR(255),
    treatment_status VARCHAR(50),
    therapist_notes TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE client_health_records (
    client_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    first_name TEXT,
    last_name TEXT,
    birthdate DATE,
    medical_condition TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE treatment_plans (
    plan_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    client_id INT,
    therapy_type TEXT,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE health_records (
    client_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    date_of_birth DATE,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    email VARCHAR(50),
    phone_number VARCHAR(15)
);

CREATE TABLE treatment_plans (
    plan_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    client_id INT,
    plan_description TEXT,
    plan_start_date DATE,
    plan_end_date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES health_records(client_id)
);

CREATE TABLE progress_reports (
    report_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    plan_id INT,
    client_id INT,
    report_date DATE,
    report_text TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (plan_id) REFERENCES treatment_plans(plan_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES health_records(client_id)
);

CREATE TABLE sessions (
    session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    client_id INT,
    plan_id INT,
    session_date DATE,
    session_type VARCHAR(50),
    session_duration INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES health_records(client_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (plan_id) REFERENCES treatment_plans(plan_id)
);

CREATE TABLE client_health_records (
    client_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    client_name VARCHAR(50),
    age INT,
    health_condition VARCHAR(100),
    date_of_birth DATE
)

CREATE TABLE treatment_plans (
    plan_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    client_id INT,
    therapist_id INT,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE,
    diagnosis VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE progress_reports (
    report_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    client_id INT,
    therapist_id INT,
    updated_at DATETIME,
    notes TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE therapists (
    therapist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    therapist_name VARCHAR(50),
    specialization VARCHAR(50)
)

CREATE TABLE appointments (
    appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    client_id INT,
    therapist_id INT,
    appointment_date DATETIME,
    status VARCHAR(20)
)
